definition.value: An amino disaccharide consisting of N-acetyl-alpha-D-galactopyranosamine and N-acetyl-beta-D-galactofuranosamine residues joined in sequence by a (1->3) glycosidic linkage.
An amino disaccharide that consists of N-acetyl-6-O-sulfo-beta-D-glucosamine having an N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl residue attached at position 4.
An amino disaccharide that consists of muramic acid having an N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl residue attached at position 4.
A dihydroxyacetophenone that is acetophenone carrying hydroxy substituents at positions 2' and 4'.
